article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 78, Rice 75
article.story: HOUSTON -- Joey Shank scored 26 points to lead Texas-San Antonio to a 78-75 victory over Rice on Thursday night. Omar Johnson added 21 points and Devin Gibson had 13 for Texas San Antonio (3-3). The victory ended the Roadrunners' 23-game nonconference road losing streak. Texas-San Antonio went ahead for good on Shank's 3-pointer that made it 67-66 with 5:24 remaining. Cory Pflieger had 21 points for Rice (2-5), while Lucas Kuipers added 14, Bryan Beasley 13 and Rodney Foster 10.
